## Finding the DebOps Source

When you need to read role defaults or playbooks, use one of these:

- **Development monorepo**: ``ansible/roles/<name>/defaults/`` at the
  root of the cloned repository

- **Ansible Collection**:
  ```sh
  ansible-galaxy collection list debops.debops
  ```
  Then ``debops/debops/roles/<name>/defaults/`` inside the path.

- **Python package**:
  ```sh
  python3 -c "import debops; print(debops.__file__)"
  ```
  Then ``roles/`` adjacent to that path.

## Read-Only Policy

Do NOT modify any files inside the DebOps source code — roles,
playbooks, or other code. All customization must be done through
inventory variables in the project directory.

If you find bugs or improvement opportunities, note them for the
user to report upstream. Do not apply fixes directly.

## Secret Data

The ``ansible/secret/`` directory (legacy) or
``ansible/views/<view>/secret/`` (modern) contains encrypted
passwords, keys, and PKI material. Do NOT read, edit, or reference
any files inside ``secret/`` directories. Exposure of secret data
to the LLM or logs is a security risk.

If a task requires access to secrets (e.g., unlocking with
``debops project unlock``), direct the user to run the necessary
commands manually.
